+### Noisy git wrapper
+
+A git wrapper on `$PATH` might write progress output to stdout even when passed
+`--quiet`. That chatter must never leak into generated plugin scripts, but it
+should stay visible on stderr so useful diagnostics aren't hidden.
+
+```zsh
+% # mock a noisy git wrapper that ignores --quiet and writes progress to stdout
+% function git { print -r -- "NOISY-GIT-WRAPPER: cloning in progress..."; mockgit "$@" }
+%
+% # the wrapper's chatter must not leak into stdout of antidote-script
+% antidote-script --kind clone noisy/repo 2>/dev/null
+%
+% # but its diagnostics are still visible on stderr
+% antidote-script --kind clone noisy/repo 2>&1 >/dev/null
+# antidote cloning noisy/repo...
+NOISY-GIT-WRAPPER: cloning in progress...
+%
+% # generated load scripts stay clean when a clone happens mid-script
+% antidote-script --kind zsh noisy/repo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/noisy/repo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/noisy/repo/repo.plugin.zsh"
+%
+% # restore the regular git mock
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
